The National Assembly has announced Senator Danjuma Laah, the senator representing Kaduna South Senatorial District, as the new Deputy Minority Whip of the 9th Senate. This was made known by the Nigerian Senate via their official Twitter page on Wednesday.  According to the tweet, “Senate President @DrAhmadLawan announces Senator Danjuma Laah as the new Deputy Minority Whip of the Ninth Senate.” Senator Laah had been the senator representing Kaduna South Senatorial District since 2015. On February 23, 2019 he was again re-elected into office having garnered 268,287 defeating Yusuf Barnabas Bala of the APC who had 133, 923 votes.